# Just Rent It

Just Rent It is a full-stack dress rental platform built with **Next.js** and **.NET**.

The system allows users to browse a dress collection, manage a favorites list, send inquiries for up to two dresses per day, receive the dress owner’s contact details by email, and download a dress catalog.

An admin interface is also provided for managing dresses, updating the catalog, handling customer inquiries, and sending monthly updates to users about the dresses they showed interest in.

## Features

### User Side
- Full user registration and login system, including JWT authentication, password encryption, Google login, and forgot password flow  
- Browse and filter a wide range of dresses  
- Lazy loading with infinite scroll for improved performance and user experience  
- Send dress inquiries and receive the dress owner’s details by email (the dress owner is notified at the same time)  
- Manage personal favorites list  
- Download the dress catalog  

### Admin Side
- Full dress management including editing and deleting dresses  
- Table view of all inquiries with inline editing and action buttons for notifying dress owners  
- Option to export the inquiries table to an Excel file  
- Send a monthly summary email to all users and dress owners with updates about dresses that were inquired about during the month  
- Update catalog content  

## Tech Stack

### Frontend
- Next.js  
- React  
- TypeScript  
- Tailwind CSS  

### Backend
- .NET / ASP.NET Web API  
- Entity Framework  
- SQL Server  

## Project Structure

- Client: Next.js frontend application  
- Server: .NET Web API backend  
- RESTful communication between client and server  

## Notes

This project was developed as part of a full-stack learning process, with a focus on clean architecture, maintainable code, performance optimization, and real-world application flow.
